M|MVP |A Mi|what do we need to learn, and what is the fastest way to learn it?
M|Conc|tx|Deliver the pd exp entirely by hand to a small number of cs. No technology. No automation. Just humans doing the work the software wld eventually do.
M|Conc|**Ho|** Find 5-10 target cs. Manually deliver the service your pd wld automate. Charge for it (or at least get commitment). Observe what cs actually value.
M|Conc|**Re|** Food on the Table founder Manuel Rosso personally created grocery lists and meal plans for one family by visiting their home, learning their preferences, and checking local store sales. He scaled from 1 to dozens of families before writing a line of code.
M|Conc|**Be|** Service-based pd, marketplace supply/demand validation, understanding workflows.
M|Conc|**St|** Deep cs in, immediate feedback, zero tc risk.
M|Conc|**Li|** Does not scale. Cannot tst tc feasibility. Labor-intensive.
M|Wiza|tx|The cs sees what appears to be a working pd, but behind the scenes, humans perform the work manually.
M|Wiza|**Ho|** bd the front-end exp (website, app, chatbot). When the cs interacts, a human fulfills the request instead of software.
M|Wiza|**Re|** Zappos founder Nick Swinmurn posted photos of shoes from local stores on a website. When someone ordered, he went to the store, bought the shoes, and shipped them. cs thought they were buying from an online retailer.
M|Wiza|**Be|** Testing demand and us exp before building the back-end. pd where the if matters but the engine is complex.
M|Wiza|**St|** Tests real purchasing behavior. Feels like a real pd. Can validate pricing.
M|Wiza|**Li|** Requires front-end bd. Hard to sustain for hi-volume use cases.
M|Smok|tx|A mk page that describes the pd and captures a commitment signal (em, pre-order, click) before the pd exists.
M|Smok|**Ho|** cr a landing page w/ a clear value proposition, feature descriptions, and a call-to-action. Drive targeted traffic. Measure conversion rate.
M|Smok|**Re|** Buffer's Joel Gascoigne created a landing page describing a sl media scheduling tool w/ a pricing page. When visitors clicked a plan, they saw "we're not quite ready yet" and an em signup. Enough signups validated demand before dv began.
M|Smok|**Be|** Validating demand and value proposition. Testing messaging and positioning. Gauging willingness to pay.
M|Smok|**St|** Fast (can be live in hours). Cheap. Generates quantitative data.
M|Smok|**Li|** Measures intent, not behavior. No pd learning. Can produce false positives w/ compelling cp.
M|Sing|tx|bd one core feature exceptionally well rather than many features poorly.
M|Sing|**Ho|** Identify the single feature that best tests your value hypothesis. bd only that feature. Strip away everything else (no settings, no profiles, no dashboards).
M|Sing|**Re|** Early Foursquare launched w/ just one feature: check-ins. No recommendations, no city guides, no br pages. Just the ability to check in at a location and see who else was there.
M|Sing|**Be|** pd where the core interaction is the hypothesis. When you need real usage data, not just intent.
M|Sing|**St|** Tests actual pd behavior. Generates real usage metrics. Can evolve into the actual pd.
M|Sing|**Li|** Requires real dv work. Risk of scope creep.
M|Piec|tx|Combine existing tools, platforms, and services to deliver the pd exp w/o building custom technology.
M|Piec|**Ho|** Stitch together Airtable, Zapier, Typeform, Calendly, Stripe, em, and other off-the-shelf tools to cr a functional pd.
M|Piec|**Re|** Groupon started as a WordPress blog w/ manually generated PDF coupons emailed to subscribers. The "platform" was a blog, an em list, and Apple Mail.
M|Piec|**Be|** Validating the full cs journey. pd that ig existing capabilities in a new way.
M|Piec|**St|** Very fast to bd. lo cost. Tests real cs behavior.
M|Piec|**Li|** Clunky us exp. Hard to scale. Maintenance overhead w/ multiple tools.
M|Vide|tx|A vd demonstration of how the pd works (or wld work), used to gauge interest and explain complex value propositions.
M|Vide|**Ho|** cr a 2-4 minute vd showing the pd in action (can be real, simulated, or animated). Share it w/ the target audience. Measure engagement, shares, signups, or pre-orders.
M|Vide|**Re|** Dropbox created a 3-minute screencast demonstrating the file-syncing exp. The vd drove their beta waitlist from 5,000 to 75,000 overnight. The pd barely worked at the time.
M|Vide|**Be|** pd w/ complex value propositions. tc pd hard to explain in text. Viral consumer pd.
M|Vide|**St|** Can go viral. Explains complex pd quickly. lo bd cost.
M|Vide|**Li|** Measures interest, not commitment. Production qual matters. Does not tst actual usage.
M|Pre-|tx|Ask cs to pay before the pd exists.
M|Pre-|**Ho|** Describe the pd. Set a price. Accept payment (or refundable deposits). Deliver later if funded.
M|Pre-|**Re|** Pebble Watch raised over $10 million on Kickstarter before manufacturing a single unit. 68,929 people pre-ordered based on renderings and a prototype vd.
M|Pre-|**Be|** Hardware pd. hi-commitment purchase decisions. Validating willingness to pay at a specific price.
M|Pre-|**St|** Strongest signal of demand (actual money). Can fund dv. Tests pricing.
M|Pre-|**Li|** Sets delivery expectations. Legal and ethical obligations. Reputational risk if you cannot deliver.
M|MVP |tx|\| Situation \| Recommended MVP tp \| Why \|
M|MVP |tx|\|-----------\|----------------------\|-----\|
M|MVP |tx|\| Uncertain if problem exists \| Concierge, Smoke tst \| Direct cs contact reveals real vs imagined problems \|
M|MVP |tx|\| Problem validated, solution uncertain \| Wizard of Oz, Single Feature \| tst the actual solution exp \|
M|MVP |tx|\| Solution clear, demand uncertain \| Smoke tst, vd, Pre-Order \| Measure mk-level interest \|
M|MVP |tx|\| Complex B2B workflow \| Concierge, Piecemeal \| Must understand workflow before automating \|
M|MVP |tx|\| Consumer mobile app \| Single Feature, vd, Smoke tst \| Consumer attention is scarce; tst one hook \|
M|MVP |tx|\| Marketplace \| Concierge (supply side), Smoke tst (demand side) \| Must validate both sides separately \|
M|MVP |tx|\| Hardware pd \| vd, Pre-Order, Wizard of Oz \| Physical prototyping is expensive; validate demand first \|
M|MVP |tx|\| ap / developer tool \| Single Feature, Piecemeal \| Developers want working tools, not promises \|
M|The |An M|
M|The |it|Can a cs understand the value proposition?
M|The |it|Can a cs take a meaningful action (sign up, pay, use)?
M|The |it|Can you distinguish signal from noise in the data?
M|The |tx|If the answer to any of these is no, the MVP is too small.
M|The |An M|
M|The |it|You are building features "while we are at it"
M|The |it|The bd phase exceeds 3-4 weeks
M|The |it|You are debating polish, edge cases, or er handling
M|The |it|You are building for scale before validating demand
M|The |tx|\| Stage \| Appropriate MVP Scope \| Time to bd \|
M|The |tx|\|-------\|----------------------\|---------------\|
M|The |tx|\| Problem validation \| Landing page, cs interviews, concierge for 5 cs \| 1-5 days \|
M|The |tx|\| Solution validation \| Wizard of Oz, clickable prototype, single feature for 20 us \| 1-3 weeks \|
M|The |tx|\| Business md validation \| Piecemeal MVP, pre-order cg, working pd for 50-100 us \| 2-4 weeks \|
M|The |tx|\| Growth validation \| Instrumented pd for 500+ us w/ A/B testing capability \| 4-8 weeks \|
