M|Mist|**Wh|** Team builds 15 features bc "us expect a complete pd." The bd takes 4 months. When it launches, they cannot tell which feature drove engagement.
M|Mist|fix|** One hypothesis per MVP. One primary metric. If you cannot explain the MVP in one sentence, it is too complex.
M|Mist|**Wh|** Team builds something minimal but shows it to no one. "We need to make it a little better first."
M|Mist|fix|** Set a launch date before you start building. Announce it publicly. Ship on that date regardless of how "ready" it feels.
M|Mist|**Wh|** Team tests the MVP w/ friends, family, or colleagues instead of actual target cs.
M|Mist|fix|** Define your early adopter profile before building. Recruit from channels where real cs exist. Friends will tell you what you want to hear.
M|Mist|**Wh|** Team launches the MVP but has no instrumentation. Learning is based on gut feel and anecdotes.
M|Mist|fix|** Define your metric and instrument the MVP before launch. Use an tools, manual tracking, or direct observation. Data collection is not optional.
M|Mist|**Wh|** Team keeps polishing bc "our br reputation is at stake." MVP never launches.
M|Mist|fix|** Remember that the MVP is for early adopters, not the mass mk. Early adopters tolerate rough edges if the core value is there. Use a separate br if reputation is a concern.
M|Mist|**Wh|** Team builds for 100,000 us when they need 100. Invests in infrastructure, sec, and compliance before validating demand.
M|Mist|fix|** Do things that do not scale. Manual processes are fine. tc debt is acceptable. Scaling problems are a luxury you earn by proving demand.
M|From|An M|
M|From|tx|\| Criterion \| Signal \| Threshold Example \|
M|From|tx|\|-----------\|--------\|-------------------\|
M|From|tx|\| Problem-Solution Fit \| cs actively use the MVP and express disappointment at the idea of losing it \| 40%+ say "very disappointed" on Sean Ellis tst \|
M|From|tx|\| Repeatable Demand \| New cs arrive through identifiable, repeatable channels \| 3+ consistent acquisition channels \|
M|From|tx|\| Willingness to Pay \| cs pay (or demonstrate clear intent) at a sustainable price point \| Positive unit economics on paper \|
M|From|tx|\| Retention \| cs return and use the pd repeatedly \| Week 4 retention above 20% (varies by category) \|
M|From|tx|\| Organic Growth \| Some cs refer others w/o prompting \| Viral coefficient above 0.2 \|
M|Grad|it|[ ] Core value hypothesis validated w/ paying cs
M|Grad|it|[ ] Growth hypothesis has initial evidence
M|Grad|it|[ ] Unit economics are viable (or have a clear path to viability)
M|Grad|it|[ ] Early adopters are retained and engaged
M|Grad|it|[ ] The team can articulate what they learned and why they are confident
M|Grad|it|[ ] At least 3 bd-Measure-Learn loops have been done
M|Grad|it|[ ] Pivot or persevere decision has been explicitly made (and persevere was chosen)
M|Grad|tx|Do not graduate the MVP prematurely. The most expensive mistake in startups is scaling something that has not been validated.